  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While the breach of trust as an accountant is significant, the amount embezzled is relatively small and partial restitution has already been made, indicating remorse and an attempt to rectify the harm. A custodial sentence of six months serves the purpose of deterrence and punishment while acknowledging the defendant's lack of criminal history and mitigating factors.",
